xfinity_mobile_arena.note: Xfinity Mobile Arena offers self-park lots with cashless payment only (credit cards, prepaid cards, Apple Pay, Google Pay), and encourages purchasing parking in advance via SpotHero for discounted rates and quickest interstate exit. Handicap accessible parking is available adjacent to east, west, and south entrances with proper vehicle designation.
xfinity_mobile_arena.rideshare: No specific rideshare notes available; check your ticket or the venue website for pickup/dropoff instructions.

wrigley_field.note: Wrigley Field offers easy-in, easy-out parking with cashless payments only; guests can reserve parking in advance through SpotHero and Cubs personnel are available on site for assistance.
wrigley_field.rideshare: No specific rideshare notes available; check your ticket or the venue website for pickup/dropoff instructions.

xl_center.note: Parking is available surrounding PeoplesBank Arena and throughout Downtown Hartford, with 45 lots and garages nearby; fans can prepurchase parking in the Hartford 21 garage and use LAZ parking reservation services for advance booking. Metered street parking is free daily from 6:00 pm to 8:00 am and all day on weekends.
xl_center.rideshare: Lyft is the official rideshare partner of PeoplesBank Arena, offering a discount code PEOPLESBANK for new users.

grand_casino_arena.note: Grand Casino Arena parking is available at two on-site ramps, RiverCentre Parking Ramp and Kellogg Parking Ramp, both connected to the complex; RiverCentre Ramp features license plate reader technology for faster cashless payment via app, QR code, or pay station, while advance parking reservations via ParkWhiz are not available for these ramps and parking is generally first come, first served.
grand_casino_arena.rideshare: Gate 4 at the northeast corner of Grand Casino Arena on 5th Street is the official rideshare pickup and drop-off location, with Lyft as the official rideshare partner offering a discount code for new users.

yankee_stadium.note: Yankee Stadium parking is available in several nearby garages and lots operated by City Parking, with prepaid parking required and rates, rules, and refunds managed by City Parking, not the Yankees. Premium Parking Passes are accepted at multiple garages including the 164th Street Garage, Ruppert Plaza Garage, 161st Street Garage, and River Avenue Garage.
yankee_stadium.rideshare: No specific rideshare notes available; check your ticket or the venue website for pickup/dropoff instructions.
